Package problemdomain

Class Shape

java.lang.Object
problemdomain.Shape
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<Shape>
public class Shape
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Shape>
This class defines the object type Shape and various properties such as the height and radius and name of shape from the file reader of the RunSort.java class.

01/10/2021

  • Constructor Details

    • Shape

      public Shape​(java.lang.String name, double firstNum, double secondNum)
      This method instantiates a Shape object and assigns it's properties as read from the file reader in the RunSort.java class. Depending on the name of the shape methods will be called to determine the radius, side, area, and volume of the shape.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the shape
      firstNum - The height value of each shape object
      secondNum - Based off the shape name, the second number will either be a assigned as a radius or side value

  • Method Details

    • assignRadius

      private double assignRadius​(java.lang.String name, double secondNum)
      This method is called by Shape depending on the name and then assigns a radius value to the shape object.
      Parameters:
      name - is the type of shape
      secondNum - is the numerical value that will be assigned as a radius
      Returns:
      value Depending on the shape the return value will be the set radius or invalid

    • assignSide

      private double assignSide​(java.lang.String name, double secondNum)
      This method is called by Shape depending on the name and then assigns a side value to the shape object.
      Parameters:
      name - is the type of shape
      secondNum - is the numerical value that will be assigned as a side
      Returns:
      depending on the shape, the return value will be the set side or invalid.
